===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], there were 3,834 people, 1,385 households, and 998 families residing in the CDP.<ref>{{Cite web|title=US Census Bureau, Table P16: Household Type |url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Lexington%20CDP,%20Washington%20p16&y=2020 |access-date=June 13, 2025 |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> The [[population density]] was {{convert|2863.33|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 1,427 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1065.72|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 81.53% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.37% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1.25% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.43% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.52% [[Race (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 3.73% from some other races and 10.17% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] people of any race were 10.51% of the population.<ref>{{Cite web|title=How many people live in Lexington CDP, Washington |url=https://data.usatoday.com/census/total-population/total-population-change/lexington-cdp-washington/160-5339230/ |access-date=June 13, 2025 |publisher=USA Today}}</ref>

